title: 2012 Bear Creek Bikes Dalton Gran Prix
2012 Smyrna Bikes - Union City Mayor's Race
US Cup East / SERC / AMBC series #3
The Athens Twilight Gambler Ride
description:
Ready to take a gamble? Up for a 50K or 100K ride through northeast Georgia\'s rolling countryside? Then Join hundreds of other cyclists for the Twilight Gambler Bike Ride Presented by Georgia Cycle Sport.

Get one playing card when you start -- three more along the way at three checkpoints that also have water, snacks, and other refreshments -- and a final card at the end of the ride to complete the hand. Cyclists with the best hands win prizes!
course: 50K or 100K options around Athens, GA and northeast Georgia
registration:
Register online: https://www.bikereg.com/Net/15407

Online Registration is $30.  Day-of registration will incur a $10 late fee.

Packet pick-up and day-of registration will begin on Friday, April 27 from 7pm-9pm in the lower level of the College  Avenue Parking Deck.  Packet pick-up and registration will also be available on Saturday, April 28 from 7:30am - 9:45am in the same location.

All riders will need to fill out and sign a USA Cycling waiver to participate.
directions:
College Avenue Parking Deck
265 College Ave
Athens, GA 30601

title: US Cup East / SERC / AMBC series #4
USA CRITS SPEED WEEK NCC Weekend
Global Imports Sandy Springs Cycling Challenge Fun
description:
Join us for a full day of family fun at the 5th Annual Global Imports Sandy Springs Cycling Challenge. 

After the ride, please enjoy the Sandy Springs Food & Wine Classic, with a variety of Sandy Springs eateries as well as wine tastings. The Food & Wine Classic begins at 11 a.m. and ends at 6 p.m.

We have the exciting finals of the SE Crits Series – “Speed Week” with some of the best Pro-Cycling that the Region will see in 2012. These great professional cyclists will fight for a purse worth tens of thousands of dollars after a week of racing around the Southeast.

Watch the Pros climb Mount Sandy Springs.
course: A 100K, metric century ride around the streets of North Atlanta.  Northside Hospital Challenge Riders will receive a technical T-Shirt and a finish line with FREE sandwiches and drinks for participating riders. All proceeds will go to support our POLICE and FIRE departments in Sandy Springs and the charities they support (Special Olympics and the Police Department Benevolent Fund).
registration:
Register online:
http://www.active.com/criterium/sandy-springs-ga/sandy-springs-cycling-challenge-2012

Entry fee is $25.  All riders will need to fill out and sign a USA Cycling waiver to participate.

title: 2012 WEST OAK RACES p/b Smyrna Bicycles
Jim Miller Grass Cyclocross Training Circuit
description:
Come join us for a beginner cyclocross clinic from 8:00am to 9:30am with focus on skills, dismounts and remounts. 

Then, at 10:00am challenge yourself in up to 4 cyclocross/short track style training blocks. Ride at race pace for 30 minute or 45 minute efforts. 

10:00am to 10:30am: block 1

10:45am to 11:15am: block 2

11:30am to 12:00pm: block 3

12:15pm to 1:00pm: block 4

Riders are welcome or ride either a mountain bike (bar ends removed) or a cyclocross bike. Helmets are mandatory. All training blocks are open categories. There will be no officials, numbers or categories. No cash or prizes are being offered for the event. The minimum age to ride is 12 years of age. There is no entry fee but donations are welcome to the Georgia Cyclocross Series to help purchase a new trailer.
course: The course will consist of a primarily grass field with short sections of dirt road. The course will be between .85 and 1.0km in length and have multiple turns. No dismounts are planned.
registration:
Please check in on the Facebook event page to let us know you are coming, or drop me a line at Bob Kuhn  bobkuhn3@netzero.com

There is a $1 fee to participate in this training event, which covers the insurance surcharge per rider.  If you enter multiple events, then you will not have to pay an extra fee to enter the additional events.  All riders must posess a USA Cycling annual license, or purchase a one day license for $5 at the event.  All riders will sign the USA Cycling event waiver on-site before the start of the event.
directions: From South: Take I-75 (North) to exit 261 towards Lockheed/Dobbins AFB. Keep left at the fork. From North: Take I-75 (South) to exit 261. Turn Right off exit. Both: Travel 6 miles, turn Right onto Austell Rd. Continue for 2 miles. Turn Right onto County Services Parkway. At the bottom of the hill turn Left onto Al Bishop Dr. Parking will be on your right approximately 1⁄4 mile.
